Quiet U-Boot output on Asahi M1: hide the board model line, gate driver
chatter via the silent= env variable, and drop the autoboot countdown
window entirely. With BOOTDELAY=0 there's no key-press window for entering
the U-Boot interactive prompt — by design — which also collapses the F4-to-
reveal-GRUB-menu timing onto GRUB's own 2-second hidden timeout, no longer
overlapping U-Boot's earlier window.

The preboot command sets silent=1 (which gates all subsequent console output
via CONFIG_SILENT_CONSOLE) and then runs `usb start` -- the same command that
was the upstream default for CONFIG_PREBOOT when CONFIG_USB_KEYBOARD=y.

U-Boot's version banner and DRAM probe line print before preboot runs, so they
remain visible; silencing those would require source edits (common/board_f.c).

Baseline: asahi-v2025.10-p1 (NOT upstream U-Boot v2025.10 -- the Asahi
packaging tag has its own defconfig deltas).

--- a/configs/apple_m1_defconfig
+++ b/configs/apple_m1_defconfig
@@ -4,7 +4,9 @@ CONFIG_ARCH_APPLE=y
 CONFIG_DEFAULT_DEVICE_TREE="t8103-j274"
 CONFIG_SYS_BOOTM_LEN=0x800000
 CONFIG_SYS_LOAD_ADDR=0x0
-CONFIG_BOOTDELAY=1
+CONFIG_BOOTDELAY=0
+CONFIG_SILENT_CONSOLE=y
+CONFIG_PREBOOT="setenv silent 1; usb start"
 # CONFIG_AUTOBOOT_KEYED is not set
 # CONFIG_AUTOBOOT_MENU_SHOW is not set
 CONFIG_BOOTCOMMAND="bootflow scan -b"
@@ -12,7 +14,7 @@ CONFIG_USE_PREBOOT=y
 CONFIG_SYS_CBSIZE=256
 CONFIG_SYS_PBSIZE=276
 # CONFIG_DISPLAY_CPUINFO is not set
-CONFIG_DISPLAY_BOARDINFO_LATE=y
+# CONFIG_DISPLAY_BOARDINFO_LATE is not set
 CONFIG_BOARD_LATE_INIT=y
 CONFIG_CMD_SELECT_FONT=y
 CONFIG_NO_NET=y
